# ACoreX Tailwind Theme & Styling

The ACoreX design system theme lives in `knowledge/theme/default.css` (source: `packages/styles/themes/default.css`). **Always style using theme tokens**, not arbitrary hex/rgb values.

## Knowledge files

| File | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `knowledge/theme/TAILWIND-GUIDE.md` | Quick reference for agents |
| `knowledge/theme/tailwind-theme.json` | Parsed tokens, utilities, patterns |
| `knowledge/theme/default.css` | Full theme source (Tailwind v4) |
| `knowledge/theme/tailwind-base.js` | Tailwind v3 preset |
| `knowledge/docs/get-started/tailwind-compatibility/` | Setup instructions |

## Required styling rules

1. **Use Tailwind utilities mapped to @theme tokens:**
   - Surfaces: `bg-lightest`, `bg-lighter`, `bg-surface`, `bg-darkest`, `text-on-lightest`, `text-on-surface`, `border-border-lightest`, `border-border-surface`
   - Semantic: `bg-primary`, `text-on-primary`, `bg-success`, `text-success`, `bg-success-100`, `text-danger-800`
   - Defaults: `bg-default`, `text-default`, `rounded-default`

   **Never append `-surface` to Tailwind utility prefixes.** CSS variables use `--ax-sys-color-lightest-surface`, but `@theme` exposes them as `--color-lightest` → use `bg-lightest`, not `bg-lightest-surface`. Same for `text-on-lightest` (not `text-on-lightest-surface`) and `border-border-lightest` (not `border-border-lightest-surface`).

   **`-surface` suffix is only for standalone `@utility` shortcut classes** that set background + text + border together, e.g. `success-surface`, `lightest-surface`, `danger-lighter-surface`. Do not combine them with `bg-*`, `text-*`, or `border-*` prefixes.

2. **Component color/look/size** — on `ax-*` components and custom hosts:
   - Size: `ax-xs`, `ax-sm`, `ax-md`, `ax-lg`, `ax-xl`
   - Color: `ax-default`, `ax-primary`, `ax-secondary`, `ax-success`, `ax-warning`, `ax-danger`
   - Look: `ax-solid`, `ax-outline`, `ax-twotone`, `ax-flat`, `ax-fill`, `ax-blank` (+ `-interactive` variants)

3. **Dark mode** — use `ax-dark` on `<html>`; apply `dark:` variants for custom markup.

   **Surface level reversal (required):** When using neutral or semantic surface-level tokens in custom markup, always pair the light token with its inverted dark counterpart via `dark:`:

   | Light (default) | Dark (`dark:`) |
   | --- | --- |
   | `lightest` | `darkest` |
   | `lighter` | `darker` |
   | `light` | `dark` |
   | `on-lightest` | `on-darkest` |
   | `on-lighter` | `on-darker` |
   | `border-lightest` | `border-darkest` |
   | `border-lighter` | `border-darker` |

   Same reversal applies to semantic palettes: `primary-lighter` → `dark:primary-darker`, `danger-lighter` → `dark:danger-darker`, etc.

   ```html
   <!-- ✅ Correct — reversed surface levels -->
   <div class="bg-lighter dark:bg-darker text-on-lightest dark:text-on-darkest">
   <div class="bg-lightest dark:bg-darkest border border-border-lightest dark:border-border-darkest">
   <div class="bg-primary-lighter/30 dark:bg-primary-darker/30">
   <div class="lightest-surface dark:darkest-surface">

   <!-- ❌ Wrong — missing dark: reversal -->
   <div class="bg-lighter text-on-lightest">
   <div class="bg-lightest border-border-lightest">
   ```

   Shade steps (`primary-500`, `secondary-500`) and base semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-primary`) do not follow this reversal — they adapt via CSS variables under `ax-dark`.

4. **Component-specific tokens** — when styling `ax-*` components, also read `tokens` from the component blueprint JSON (`--ax-comp-*` variables).

5. **Never** invent colors outside the theme. If a token is missing, use the closest palette step (50–950) or surface level.

## Examples

```html
<!-- Layout with neutral surface -->
<div class="bg-lightest dark:bg-darkest text-on-lightest dark:text-on-darkest border border-border-lightest dark:border-border-darkest p-4 rounded-default">

<!-- Semantic block -->
<div class="bg-primary-50 text-primary-900 border border-primary-200 p-3">

<!-- Component host styling -->
<ax-button class="ax-md ax-primary ax-solid">Save</ax-button>
```

## Setup (consumer projects)

```css
@import '@acorex/styles/themes/default.css';
```

For Tailwind v3: `presets: [require('@acorex/styles/tailwind-base.js')]`
